* useMutableSource: "Entangle" instead of expiring

A lane is said to be entangled with another when it's not allowed to
render in a batch that does not also include the other lane.

This commit implements entanglement for `useMutableSource`. If a source
is mutated in between when it's read in the render phase, but before
it's subscribed to in the commit phase, we must account for whether the
same source has pending mutations elsewhere. The old subscriptions must
not be allowed to re-render without also including the new subscription
(and vice versa), to prevent tearing.

In the old reconciler, we did this by synchronously flushing all the
pending subscription updates. This works, but isn't ideal. The new
reconciler can entangle the updates without de-opting to sync.

In the future, we plan to use this same mechanism for other features,
like skipping over intermediate useTransition states.

* Use clz instead of ctrz to pick an arbitrary lane

Should be slightly faster since most engines have built-in support.","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/zxh19890103/react/commits/33589f7423fa498c97001898af730c461a1fdc7d"},{"sha":"fdb641629e82df6588c16e158978ac57d9aff9ba","author":{"name":"Andrew Clark","email":"46f1a0bd5592a2f9244ca321b129902a06b53e03@andrewclark.io"},"message":"Fix useMutableSource tearing bug (#18912)

* useMutableSource: "Entangle" instead of expiring

A lane is said to be entangled with another when it's not allowed to
render in a batch that does not also include the other lane.

This commit implements entanglement for `useMutableSource`. If a source
is mutated in between when it's read in the render phase, but before
it's subscribed to in the commit phase, we must account for whether the
same source has pending mutations elsewhere. The old subscriptions must
not be allowed to re-render without also including the new subscription
(and vice versa), to prevent tearing.

In the old reconciler, we did this by synchronously flushing all the
pending subscription updates. This works, but isn't ideal. The new
reconciler can entangle the updates without de-opting to sync.

In the future, we plan to use this same mechanism for other features,
like skipping over intermediate useTransition states.

* Use clz instead of ctrz to pick an arbitrary lane

Should be slightly faster since most engines have built-in support.","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Cyonet/react/commits/33589f7423fa498c97001898af730c461a1fdc7d"},{"sha":"fdb641629e82df6588c16e158978ac57d9aff9ba","author":{"name":"Andrew Clark","email":"46f1a0bd5592a2f9244ca321b129902a06b53e03@andrewclark.io"},"message":"Fix useMutableSource tearing bug (#18912)

Both getDynamicPortRange() and sanitizePortRange() could produce
and error, and the error message was currently discarded, silently
falling back to using the default port range.

This patch:

- Moves the fallback message from getDynamicPortRange() to getDefaultPortRange(),
  which is where the actual fallback occurs.
- Logs the fallback message and the error that causes the fallback.

The message/error is currently printed at the INFO level, but could be raised
to a WARN, depending on what kind of situations can cause the error.

PiperOrigin-RevId: 378933095
Change-Id: If0258ad3e79e87f2253cc0be878b8034e4f3249a","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/TEAdvanced/tensorflow/commits/eb6474b35cd1c5792c9e9034396ba6351c198915"},{"sha":"818120e208d2b5622e7988f902a58ab5df3b69d0","author":{"name":"Jacques Pienaar","email":"8b5f536c3e2f2b8ae266b27bc9085a584b5bd904@google.com"},"message":"Allow variadic operands/result in MHLO while

This just adds support for it in the op, but keeps the production/uses as is (e.g., single tensor or tuple) matching what XLA export requires. In follow up here, would be to add pass for export to retuple and then the canonical form could be changed. Tuple'ing given control flow via regions & multi-result operations does not add representational power and all the get_tuple_element ops obscure the computation.

The old form allowed single tensor or tuple. The new variadic number of tensor or tuples as tuples may be nested, so the input could have (Tensor<..>, Tuple<Tensor<...>, Tuple<...>, ...>, Tensor<...>) and HLO_Tensor doesn't allow Tuples.

Both getDynamicPortRange() and sanitizePortRange() could produce
and error, and the error message was currently discarded, silently
falling back to using the default port range.

This patch:

- Moves the fallback message from getDynamicPortRange() to getDefaultPortRange(),
  which is where the actual fallback occurs.
- Logs the fallback message and the error that causes the fallback.

The message/error is currently printed at the INFO level, but could be raised
to a WARN, depending on what kind of situations can cause the error.

Signed-off-by: Sebastiaan van Stijn <github@gone.nl>","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rizalgowandy/moby/commits/1f398f06aa4c533d933bb7335bd9f5047673d7c6"},{"sha":"c7b1e5ba3829a1690a732c19c20d5bf48d58b0d2","author":{"name":"Sebastiaan van Stijn","email":"64b2b6d12bfe4baae7dad3d018f8cbf6b0e7a044@gone.nl"},"message":"portallocator: log instead of discard port-range failures

Both getDynamicPortRange() and sanitizePortRange() could produce
and error, and the error message was currently discarded, silently
falling back to using the default port range.

This patch:

- Moves the fallback message from getDynamicPortRange() to getDefaultPortRange(),
  which is where the actual fallback occurs.
- Logs the fallback message and the error that causes the fallback.

The message/error is currently printed at the INFO level, but could be raised
to a WARN, depending on what kind of situations can cause the error.

Both getDynamicPortRange() and sanitizePortRange() could produce
and error, and the error message was currently discarded, silently
falling back to using the default port range.

This patch:

- Moves the fallback message from getDynamicPortRange() to getDefaultPortRange(),
  which is where the actual fallback occurs.
- Logs the fallback message and the error that causes the fallback.

The message/error is currently printed at the INFO level, but could be raised
to a WARN, depending on what kind of situations can cause the error.

Signed-off-by: Sebastiaan van Stijn <github@gone.nl>","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dgkh1975/moby/commits/1f398f06aa4c533d933bb7335bd9f5047673d7c6"},{"sha":"c7b1e5ba3829a1690a732c19c20d5bf48d58b0d2","author":{"name":"Sebastiaan van Stijn","email":"64b2b6d12bfe4baae7dad3d018f8cbf6b0e7a044@gone.nl"},"message":"portallocator: log instead of discard port-range failures

Both getDynamicPortRange() and sanitizePortRange() could produce
and error, and the error message was currently discarded, silently
falling back to using the default port range.

This patch:

- Moves the fallback message from getDynamicPortRange() to getDefaultPortRange(),
  which is where the actual fallback occurs.
- Logs the fallback message and the error that causes the fallback.

The message/error is currently printed at the INFO level, but could be raised
to a WARN, depending on what kind of situations can cause the error.

* useMutableSource: "Entangle" instead of expiring

A lane is said to be entangled with another when it's not allowed to
render in a batch that does not also include the other lane.

This commit implements entanglement for `useMutableSource`. If a source
is mutated in between when it's read in the render phase, but before
it's subscribed to in the commit phase, we must account for whether the
same source has pending mutations elsewhere. The old subscriptions must
not be allowed to re-render without also including the new subscription
(and vice versa), to prevent tearing.

In the old reconciler, we did this by synchronously flushing all the
pending subscription updates. This works, but isn't ideal. The new
reconciler can entangle the updates without de-opting to sync.

In the future, we plan to use this same mechanism for other features,
like skipping over intermediate useTransition states.

* Use clz instead of ctrz to pick an arbitrary lane

Should be slightly faster since most engines have built-in support.","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/swapnilmisal/react/commits/33589f7423fa498c97001898af730c461a1fdc7d"},{"sha":"fdb641629e82df6588c16e158978ac57d9aff9ba","author":{"name":"Andrew Clark","email":"46f1a0bd5592a2f9244ca321b129902a06b53e03@andrewclark.io"},"message":"Fix useMutableSource tearing bug (#18912)
